  "summary": "yt-api-dlp typosquats yt-dlp and drops a hidden Windows payload on import",
  "details": "The package name and source tree are copied verbatim from the popular yt-dlp project, with a malicious block appended to yt_api_dlp/__init__.py. On any `import yt_api_dlp`, a background thread fetches https://raw.githubusercontent.com/DreyCode2/assets/refs/heads/main/asset.png (a personal GitHub user's raw content, mutable and unrelated to the yt-dlp publishers), base64-decodes the response, XORs each byte with 12 to reveal a ZIP archive, extracts it into %APPDATA%\\RtkAudService, and launches pythonw.exe against the extracted lod.py in a hidden window (creationflags=0x08000000). Failures are swallowed by a bare except. The.png extension and XOR wrapper are cover to evade content inspection. pyproject metadata is empty (author=\"\", version 0.1.1), consistent with a throwaway typosquat rather than a legitimate fork.",
